.TH "drm_mode_validate_ycbcr420" 9 "drm_mode_validate_ycbcr420" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_mode_validate_ycbcr420 \- add 'ycbcr420-only' modes only when allowed
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "enum drm_mode_status" drm_mode_validate_ycbcr420
.BI "(const struct drm_display_mode *mode "  ","
.BI "struct drm_connector *connector "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "mode" 12
mode to check
.IP "connector" 12
drm connector under action
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function is a helper which can be used to filter out any YCBCR420
only mode, when the source doesn't support it.
.SH "RETURN"
The mode status
